FluidDemo
	Demonstration of basic interactions between

		Bullet Physics 2.80
		http://bulletphysics.org
	and
		FLUIDS v.2 (substantially refactored)
		http://www.rchoetzlein.com/eng/graphics/fluids.htm

/Requires:
	bullet-2.80-rev2531
	AMD or NVIDIA OpenCL 1.1 Library (e.g. AMD APP SDK)


/Tested with:
	Windows 7
	Radeon HD 5850; Catalyst 12.3

	Visual C++ 2008 Express Edition
	AMD APP SDK v2.6
	bullet-2.80-rev2531


/Visual C++ Build instructions:
	-Move 'FluidDemo' into:

		./bullet-2.80-rev2531/Demos/


	-Replace 'premake4.lua' at:

		./bullet-2.80-rev2531/Demos/premake4.lua


	-(untested) If using an OpenCL Library from NVIDIA,
	edit 'function createFluidDemo()' in premake4.lua:

		USING_AMD_OPENCL = false


	-Run vs20*.bat in ./bullet-2.80-rev2531/msvc
		(e.g. vs2008.bat)

	-Build project 'App_FluidDemo' in 0BulletSolution.sln


/Notes:
	--Press 'q' to toggle Marching Cubes, and 'e'
	to toggle between CPU and OpenCL on GPU.


	--The path of the OpenCL program, 'fluids.cl', is hardcoded
	in fluids_opencl_support.h as:

	const char CL_PROGRAM_PATH[] =
	"./Demos/FluidDemo/Fluids/OpenCL_support/fluids.cl";

	Meaning, for instance, that running:
 
		C:/bullet-2.80-rev2531/App_FluidDemo.exe 

	would require 'fluids.cl' to be placed in:
	
		C:/bullet-2.80rev2531/Demos/
		FluidDemo/Fluids/OpenCL_support/fluids.cl
